# Part 6 – Modulus (%)

One of the most useful operators.

```python
print(10 % 3)
```

Output

```text
1
```

Why?

Because

```text
10 ÷ 3

Quotient = 3

Remainder = 1
```

So

```python
10 % 3
```

means

> Give me the remainder.

---

Another example

```python
print(20 % 5)
```

Output

```text
0
```

Because

```text
20 ÷ 5

Remainder = 0
```

---

# Why is `%` useful?

Imagine checking if an age is even.

```python
age = 36

if age % 2 == 0:
    print("Even Age")
else:
    print("Odd Age")
```

